                <h1>D-Day: The Turning Point of WWII</h1>
                <p>D-Day, June 6, 1944, marked a pivotal moment in World War II as Allied forces launched a massive invasion on Nazi-occupied France. With over 156,000 troops landing on the beaches of Normandy, it was the largest seaborne invasion in history. The success of D-Day was instrumental in the liberation of Western Europe from Nazi control.</p>
